1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3500.2 of Title 56, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The purpose of the Streamlined Services Act is to establish
5 a unified and streamlined eligibility and enrollment system within
6 the Oklahoma Department of Human Services to improve access to and
7 management of services for Oklahomans.
8 B. The system shall promote efficiency, accessibility, and
9 coordination of services across programs, including but not limited
10 to:
11 1. Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP);
12 2. Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (TANF);
13 3. Child Care Subsidies;
14 4. Low Income Home Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP);
15 5. Medicaid; and
16 6. Women, Infants, and Children (WIC).
17 C. The Department shall coordinate with the Oklahoma Health
18 Care Authority, the State Department of Health, and any other state
19 agency or community partner that administers a program specified in
20 subsection B of this section to implement the provisions of this
21 act.
22 D. The Department shall conduct a feasibility study to identify
23 opportunities to integrate additional programs into the system over
24 time.
